## 📚 Room Summary
This room explained what DNS(Domain Name System) means and how it works. It covers what happens when you make a DNS request, the five common DNS record types (A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, TXT)
and domain heiarchy including top-level domain (TLD), second-level domain, and the subdomain.
The pratical part consisted of making request for DNS quarrys on a external website to see the results of different request
---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned
- How DNS works and operates
- Made DNS request on a website

